{
  "Linear Programming": "线线性规划",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "Maximize P = 3x + 5y subject to x + y ≤ 10, x ≥ 0, y ≥ 0. The vertices are (0,0), (10,0), and (0,10). What is the maximum P?": "最大 P = 3x + 5y 受 x + y = 10, x = 0, y = 0。 顶部是 (0,0, (10,0) 和 (0,10) 。",
  "Evaluate P at each vertex: P(0,0)=0, P(10,0)=30, P(0,10)=50. The maximum is P=50 at (0,10).": "每个顶点的评价P:P(0,0)=0,P(10,0)=30,P(0,10)=50。最大值为P=50(0,10)。",
  "Minimize C = 4x + 3y at vertices (1,2), (5,1), (4,5), (2,4). What is the minimum C?": "最小化 C = 4x + 3y 顶点(1 2), (5 1), (4 5), (2 4) 最小化 C = 4x + 3y 。",
  "C(1,2)=4+6=10, C(5,1)=20+3=23, C(4,5)=16+15=31, C(2,4)=8+12=20. Minimum is 10 at (1,2).": "C(1,2)=4+6=10,C(5,1)=20+3=23,C(4,5)=16+15=31,C(2,4)=8+12=20,最低值为10(1,2)",
  "What is linear programming?": "什么是线性编程?",
  "Linear programming is a mathematical optimization technique that finds the maximum or minimum value of a linear function subject to a set of linear inequality constraints.": "线性编程是一种数学优化技术,它发现线性函数的最大或最低值受一系列线性不平等制约。",
  "What is an objective function?": "什么是客观功能?",
  "The objective function is the linear expression (like P = 3x + 5y) that represents the quantity to be optimized. It is evaluated at each vertex of the feasible region to find the optimal value.": "目标函数是表示要优化的数量的线性表达式(如 P = 3x + 5y),在可行区域的每个顶端进行评估,以找到最佳值。",
  "What is a constraint in linear programming?": "线性方案规划的制约因素是什么?",
  "Constraints are linear inequalities that model real-world limitations such as available resources, budget limits, or minimum requirements. Together they define the feasible region.": "制约因素是线性不平等,它们模拟了现实世界的限制,例如现有资源、预算限制或最低要求,它们共同界定了可行的区域。",
  "What is the feasible region?": "什么是可行的区域?",
  "The feasible region is the intersection of all constraint half-planes. It is the set of all points (x, y) that satisfy every constraint, and the optimal solution lies within or on its boundary.": "可行的区域是所有制约半空机的交叉点,所有点(x、y)的组合满足了每一种制约,最佳解决办法在其边界内或边界上。",
  "What is the Corner Point Theorem?": "角点定理是什么?",
  "The Corner Point Theorem guarantees that on a bounded polygonal feasible region, the maximum and minimum of a linear objective function occur at vertices. This allows checking only finitely many points.": "角点理论保证在一个交界的多边形可行区域,线性目标功能的最大和最小值出现在顶端。 这样只能对很多点进行有限的检查。",
  "What is a vertex of the feasible region?": "可行区域的顶点是什么?",
  "A vertex is a corner point of the feasible region formed by the intersection of two or more constraint boundaries. These are the candidate points for the optimal solution.": "顶点是两个或两个以上制约边界交叉形成的可行区域的角点,是最佳解决办法的候选点。",
  "What is an infeasible problem?": "什么是不可行的问题?",
  "An infeasible problem has contradictory constraints, so no point satisfies all of them. The feasible region is empty, and no optimal solution exists.": "一个不可行的问题有自相矛盾的制约,因此没有一点能满足所有这些制约。 可行的区域是空的,不存在最佳解决方案。",
  "What is a bounded feasible region?": "什么是有边界的可行区域?",
  "A bounded feasible region is enclosed on all sides and does not extend to infinity. Both the maximum and minimum of the objective function are guaranteed to exist in a bounded region.": "各方都封闭着一个有边界的可行区域,但不会扩大到无限,保证在一个有边界的区域存在最大和最低的客观功能。",
  "A shipping company uses small vans (capacity 50 boxes, cost $100/trip) and large trucks (capacity 200 boxes, cost $300/trip). They must ship at least 1000 boxes with at most 8 vehicles. What is the minimum cost?": "航运公司使用小型货车(50箱容量,每辆100美元,每辆100美元)和大型卡车(200箱容量,每辆300美元,每辆300美元)。",
  "50v + 200t ≥ 1000, v + t ≤ 8, v,t ≥ 0. C = 100v + 300t. At (0,5): 1000 boxes shipped, cost = 300(5) = $1,500. At (4,4): cost = 400+1200 = $1,600. Minimum is $1,500.": "50v + 200t □ 1000, v + t □ 8, v, t □ 0. C = 100v + 300t. 时( 0, 5): 发运1 000箱, 费用= 300(5) = 1 500美元. 时( 4, 4): 费用= 400+1200 = 1 600美元. 最低为 1 500美元.",
  "A company makes desks ($50 profit) and chairs ($30 profit). Assembly: desk = 4 hrs, chair = 2 hrs (80 hrs available). Finishing: desk = 2 hrs, chair = 3 hrs (90 hrs available). What is the maximum profit?": "一个公司制造办公桌(50美元利润)和椅子(30美元利润),组装:办公桌=4小时,椅子=2小时(80小时可用),完工:办公桌=2小时,椅子=3小时(90小时可用)。",
  "4d + 2c ≤ 80, 2d + 3c ≤ 90. Intersection of boundary lines: d = 7.5, c = 25. P(7.5, 25) = 375 + 750 = $1,125. This exceeds P(20,0) = $1,000 and P(0,30) = $900.": "90. 边界线的交界点:d=7.5,c=25,P(7.5,25)=375+750=1 125,超过P(20,0)=1 000美元,P(0)=900美元。",
  "A toy store orders dolls ($5 cost, $12 revenue) and cars ($3 cost, $7 revenue). The budget is $300 and storage fits 80 items. How many of each maximizes revenue?": "玩具商店订货娃娃(5美元,12美元收入)和汽车(3美元,7美元收入)预算为300美元,储存80件。 每项有多少是收入最大化?",
  "5d + 3c ≤ 300, d + c ≤ 80, d,c ≥ 0. R = 12d + 7c. Vertices: (0,0), (60,0), (0,80). Intersection: 5d+3(80-d)=300, 2d=60, d=30, c=50. R(30,50)=360+350=710, R(60,0)=720, R(0,80)=560. Max = $720.": "5d + 3c = 300, d + c = 80, d, c = 0. 0. R = 12d + 7c. 口号: (0,0, (60,0, 0, 0, 0, 80) , 中间部分: 5d + 3(80-d) = 300, 2d= 60, d= 30, c = 50. R(30, 50) = 360+350= 710, R(60,0) = 720, R(0,80) = 560. 最大 = 720。"
}